  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Description&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Effectively drive down infrastructure costs associated with legacy applications. Infrastructure costs include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Maintenance costs for software and hardware&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Software licenses&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Servers&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Power and facilities&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Symptoms&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Symptoms that indicate the need to reduce infrastructure costs include the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Multiple&amp;nbsp;infrastructures to support multiple platforms (server sprawl)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Infrastructure is costly and difficult to be maintained&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Duplication of data across servers&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Solutions&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
